metadata.name: The Triad of Power
metadata.description:
Fear, Rage, and Anger were three entities that roamed the land, causing chaos and destruction wherever they went. People lived in constant terror of the three, never knowing when they would strike next.

Despite the efforts of some brave individuals who tried to stand up to them, the three entities remained unvanquished, their powers only growing stronger. And as time passed, the land became consumed by fear, rage, and anger, until there was nothing left but darkness and despair.

In the end, the people were consumed by their own fears, succumbing to the power of the three entities. The land was plunged into eternal darkness, and Fear, Rage, and Anger ruled supreme, their powers unchallenged. It was a bleak and hopeless ending, a warning to all who dared to resist the forces of fear, rage, and anger.
